**Damage Report:**

**Vehicle Make/Model:** Not specified (only the rear fender is visible)

**Location of Damage:** Rear fender

**Type of Damage:** The rear fender appears to have multiple scratches and dents. The scratches are linear and seem to be caused by impact or scraping against a hard surface. There are also some areas where the paint has been chipped away, revealing the underlying metal.

**Additional Notes:**
- The damage seems to be concentrated on the lower portion of the fender.
- The surrounding area of the fender looks intact with no signs of additional damage.
- The tire and wheel well appear undamaged.

**Conclusion:**
The vehicle has sustained damage to the rear fender, which includes scratches, dents, and chipped paint. Further inspection may be necessary to determine the extent of the damage and any underlying structural issues that could be hidden beneath the surface.

**Recommendation:**
It is recommended to have a professional mechanic inspect the vehicle thoroughly to assess the full extent of the damage and provide an accurate estimate for repairs.
